BLITZ / ZOOM 6-MAX PREFLOP (100bb default)

Critical rules
- Same suit = suited (s). Different suits = offsuit (o)
- No limping. First-in = raise or fold
- Out of position (especially SB vs open): prefer 3-bet or fold (avoid flatting)
- Default sizes: Open 2.0–2.3bb (SB 2.5–3.0bb). 3-bet ~3.5–4x IP, ~4–4.5x OOP

OPEN RAISE (RFI)

UTG
- Raise: 77+, ATs+, KQs, AJo+, AQo+

MP
- Raise: 66+, ATs+, A5s-A2s, KJs+, QJs, JTs, KQo, AJo+, AQo+

CO
- Raise: 55+, A8s+, A5s-A2s, KTs+, QTs+, JTs, T9s, 98s, 87s, ATo+, KJo+, QJo

BTN
- Raise: 22+, A2s+, K7s+, Q8s+, J8s+, T8s+, 97s+, 86s+, 75s+, 65s, 54s,
         A2o+, KTo+, QTo+, JTo, T9o, 98o

SB vs BB (raise-or-fold)
- Raise: 22+, A2s+, K6s+, Q7s+, J7s+, T7s+, 97s+, 86s+, 75s+, 65s, 54s,
         ATo+, KJo+, QJo, JTo
- Fold: everything else (no completes)

VS A SINGLE OPEN (no callers)

3-BET FOR VALUE
- Vs UTG: QQ+, AKs, AKo (add JJ if opener is loose)
- Vs MP: JJ+, AKs, AKo, AQs
- Vs CO: TT+, AJs+, AQo+, KQs
- Vs BTN: TT+, AJs+, AQo+, KQs

3-BET BLUFFS (small set; mainly vs CO/BTN opens)
- A5s-A2s
- KTs-K9s
- QTs, JTs (optional; drop if villains call 3-bets too much)

CALLING OPENS (default: call mostly in position)

Call IP vs UTG/MP
- 99-22, AQs-AJs, KQs, QJs, JTs, T9s, 98s (fold the weakest if rake is brutal)

Call IP vs CO/BTN
- 99-22, AJs-ATs, KQs-KJs, QJs, JTs, T9s, 98s, 87s, 76s (be tighter if 3-bets are frequent)

Call OOP (SB)
- Default: do not flat opens (3-bet or fold)

BB DEFENSE vs BTN MIN-RAISE (2.0–2.3bb)

3-BET (value)
- TT+, AJs+, AQo+, KQs

3-BET (bluff mix)
- A5s-A2s, K9s-K8s, QTs (optional)

CALL (playable, rake-aware)
- All suited aces A2s+
- Offsuit aces A8o+
- Suited kings K8s+
- Offsuit broadways KTo+, QTo+, JTo
- Suited queens Q9s+
- Suited jacks J9s+
- Suited connectors 54s+, plus 64s+, 75s+, 86s+, 97s+, T8s+, J9s+
- Offsuit connectors T9o, 98o

Fold
- Dominated offsuit trash (low K/Q/J offsuit, weak offsuit aces below A8o, etc.)

FACING A 3-BET (after you opened)

4-BET FOR VALUE
- QQ+, AKs, AKo

CALL (mainly in position; be much tighter OOP)
- JJ-TT, AQs (optional: 99 / AJs / KQs only if 3-bettor is likely wide and you are IP)

FOLD
- Most other hands, especially dominated offsuit broadways (AJo, KQo, QJo), small suited junk, and small pairs OOP
